{
  "stem": "719.1",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "How in the world will you go?",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So my aunt, she knew the city well, so she got in touch with a guy, like, a horse and carriage guy, but it wasn't just a carriage, it was like a wagon with horses.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And, right away, people were trying to make business, to do something.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So he was, like, the next best transportation.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "So apparently, he gathered some other people that were vacationing in this town, so he put us on that wagon.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "It was like a wagon, and it was hours of driving, with horses.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "It was quite a few hours by transportation like that.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And my aunt said goodbye to me with tears in her eyes, and crying, and she says, I'm putting you on this wagon, and I don't even know if you have someone to, to find.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But if you insist so much you do want to go, and I don't want to feel responsible.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Whatever, we don't know what's going to happen to them.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And unfortunately, they, they never survived, you see.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So I'm on that wagon, and what my aunt did, which was amazing-- this was September, and I'll never forget-- it was close to the Jewish holidays, close to Rosh Hashanah and Yom Kippur.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And she knew, if my parents are alive, they probably won't have a live chicken, or something to-- for the holidays.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So it's something amazing.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Children these days would never believe.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "She took a briefcase, a regular briefcase, and she tied the legs from the chicken.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "She stuck the little head out through the opening from the briefcase, so that the chicken is alive while I, if I get home, when I get home.",
      "word_count": 28
    }
  ],
